sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard
    participant KubeflowCtrl as Kubeflow Notebook<br/>Controller
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod<br/>(StatefulSet)
    participant DSPAPI as DS Pipelines<br/>API Server
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow<br/>Controller
    participant S3 as Object Storage<br/>(S3)

    Note over User,S3: Workflow 1: Notebook Development → Pipeline Execution

    User->>Dashboard: Login via Gateway OAuth2/OIDC<br/>(kube-auth-proxy validates)
    Dashboard-->>User: Show projects and workbenches
    User->>Dashboard: Create project, launch notebook workbench
    Dashboard->>KubeflowCtrl: Create Notebook CR in user namespace

    KubeflowCtrl->>Notebook: Create StatefulSet + Service
    KubeflowCtrl->>KubeflowCtrl: Create HTTPRoute (cross-ns)<br/>+ ReferenceGrant<br/>+ inject kube-rbac-proxy sidecar

    User->>Notebook: Access via Gateway HTTPRoute<br/>(OAuth2 + kube-rbac-proxy)
    Notebook->>S3: Download training data<br/>(HTTPS, AWS IAM or static creds)
    Note over Notebook: Develop ML code,<br/>define KFP pipeline<br/>using kfp SDK
    Notebook->>S3: Upload model artifacts

    User->>DSPAPI: Submit pipeline via kfp SDK<br/>(Bearer token forwarding)
    DSPAPI->>S3: Store pipeline definition<br/>(SeaweedFS/MinIO)
    DSPAPI->>Argo: Create Argo Workflow
    Argo->>Argo: Execute pipeline steps as container pods
    Argo-->>DSPAPI: Report step completion<br/>(persistence agent)
    DSPAPI-->>User: Pipeline run complete

