sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Model Registry
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard
    participant LLMCtrl as llmisvc-controller<br/>-manager
    participant ODHModel as odh-model-controller
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>(Envoy)
    participant EPP as gateway-api-inference<br/>-extension (EPP)
    participant vLLM as vLLM Pod<br/>(+ scheduler sidecar)
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 2: LLM Model Serving (KServe + llm-d)

    User->>Dashboard: Create LLMInferenceService CR<br/>(specify model, runtime, resources)
    Dashboard->>LLMCtrl: LLMInferenceService CR created

    LLMCtrl->>LLMCtrl: Apply LLMInferenceServiceConfig template
    LLMCtrl->>vLLM: Create InferencePool + Deployment<br/>(vLLM container + scheduler sidecar<br/>+ optional KV cache sidecar)
    LLMCtrl->>LLMCtrl: Create TLS certs, ConfigMaps, Services

    ODHModel->>ODHModel: Watch InferenceService (delta processing)
    ODHModel->>Gateway: Create HTTPRoute for model endpoint
    ODHModel->>ODHModel: Create ServiceMonitor,<br/>KEDA TriggerAuthentication,<br/>Envoy filters

    Note over vLLM: Pull runtime image from<br/>container registry (quay.io)
    vLLM->>vLLM: Download model from S3<br/>(AWS IAM auth)
    vLLM->>vLLM: Load model into GPU memory

    Client->>Gateway: POST predict endpoint<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS 1.3)
    Gateway->>EPP: ext_proc filter invocation
    EPP->>vLLM: Scrape model server metrics
    Note over EPP: Select optimal pod:<br/>load-aware routing,<br/>prefix-cache-aware,<br/>SLO-based deadline ordering
    EPP-->>Gateway: Route to selected pod
    Gateway->>vLLM: Forward request<br/>(HTTP, optional pod-to-pod TLS)
    vLLM->>vLLM: Run inference on GPU
    vLLM-->>Gateway: Prediction response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response<br/>(HTTPS/443)

