sequenceDiagram
    participant User as API Consumer
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>(Envoy)
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant / Authorino
    participant BBR as AI Gateway Payload<br/>Processing (BBR)
    participant MaaSAPI as MaaS API
    participant MaaSCtrl as MaaS Controller
    participant Provider as External AI Provider<br/>(Anthropic, Azure,<br/>Vertex, Bedrock)

    Note over User,Provider: Workflow 3: Models as a Service (Multi-Provider)

    MaaSCtrl->>MaaSCtrl: Reconcile Tenant CR
    MaaSCtrl->>MaaSAPI: Deploy maas-api instance
    MaaSCtrl->>BBR: Deploy payload-processing
    MaaSCtrl->>Authorino: Deploy Authorino + AuthPolicies
    MaaSCtrl->>MaaSCtrl: Deploy Perses dashboards

    User->>MaaSAPI: Create ExternalModel CR<br/>(map model name → provider)
    User->>MaaSAPI: Create MaaSAuthPolicy<br/>(API key or OIDC rules)

    User->>Gateway: POST OpenAI-compatible request<br/>(HTTPS/443, API key in header)
    Gateway->>Authorino: ext_authz evaluation
    Note over Authorino: Priority evaluation:<br/>1. API key<br/>2. OpenShift token<br/>3. External OIDC JWT<br/>+ OPA Rego rules
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: Validate subscription
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK<br/>(strip Authorization header)

    Gateway->>BBR: ext_proc body parsing
    Note over BBR: Resolve model → provider mapping<br/>Inject API keys from K8s Secrets<br/>Translate OpenAI → provider format<br/>(e.g., OpenAI → Anthropic Messages API)
    BBR-->>Gateway: Transformed request

    Gateway->>Provider: Forward to external provider<br/>(HTTPS/443, provider API key)
    Provider-->>Gateway: Provider-native response
    Gateway->>BBR: ext_proc response translation
    BBR-->>Gateway: OpenAI-compatible response
    Gateway-->>User: Unified OpenAI response<br/>(HTTPS/443)

