sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard /<br/>codeflare-sdk
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant AuthCtrl as KubeRay Authentication<br/>Controller
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>(Envoy)
    participant Head as RayCluster<br/>Head Pod
    participant Workers as RayCluster<br/>Worker Pods

    Note over User,Workers: Workflow 4: Distributed Training with KubeRay

    User->>Dashboard: Submit RayJob or RayCluster CR<br/>(specify resources, image, script)
    Dashboard->>KubeRay: Create RayCluster CR in user namespace

    KubeRay->>KubeRay: Validate AuthenticationReady condition
    KubeRay->>Head: Create head pod + Service<br/>(inject mTLS certs if enabled)
    KubeRay->>Workers: Create worker pods<br/>(autoscaler manages count)

    AuthCtrl->>Gateway: Create HTTPRoute in platform NS<br/>(cross-namespace reference)
    AuthCtrl->>AuthCtrl: Create ReferenceGrant in user NS<br/>(reference counting for shared grants)
    AuthCtrl->>AuthCtrl: Create kube-rbac-proxy RBAC

    Head->>Workers: Coordinate distributed training<br/>(Ray internal gRPC)
    Workers->>Workers: Execute training tasks<br/>(GPU-accelerated)

    User->>Gateway: Access Ray Dashboard<br/>(HTTPS/443, OAuth2 + kube-rbac-proxy)
    Gateway->>Head: Forward to Ray Dashboard<br/>(HTTP/8265)
    Head-->>User: Training progress, metrics,<br/>resource utilization

