sequenceDiagram
    participant User as ML Engineer
    participant Dashboard as odh-dashboard
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>Operator
    participant LMEvalPod as LMEval Pod<br/>(driver + evaluator)
    participant ModelEndpoint as Model Endpoint<br/>(KServe)
    participant MLflow as MLflow
    participant Guardrails as FMS Guardrails<br/>Orchestrator
    participant Client as Inference Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 5: Model Evaluation and Guardrails

    User->>Dashboard: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>(specify model, tasks, batch size)
    Dashboard->>TrustyAI: LMEvalJob CR created

    TrustyAI->>LMEvalPod: Create evaluation pod:<br/>driver init container +<br/>lm-eval main container +<br/>optional GPU sidecar
    LMEvalPod->>ModelEndpoint: Run evaluation harness<br/>against model endpoint
    LMEvalPod->>TrustyAI: Report progress via<br/>driver HTTP API (port 18080)
    Note over LMEvalPod: Execute lm-evaluation-harness<br/>tasks (accuracy, perplexity, etc.)

    LMEvalPod-->>TrustyAI: Evaluation complete
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Write results to<br/>LMEvalJob CR status
    TrustyAI->>MLflow: Log evaluation metrics<br/>(optional)

    Note over Guardrails,Client: At serving time (independent flow)

    Client->>Guardrails: Inference request<br/>(intercepted by orchestrator)
    Guardrails->>Guardrails: Call guardrails detectors:<br/>NeMo, regex, built-in rules<br/>(input safety check)
    Guardrails->>ModelEndpoint: Forward safe request
    ModelEndpoint-->>Guardrails: Model response
    Guardrails->>Guardrails: Output safety check<br/>(NeMo, regex, built-in rules)
    Guardrails-->>Client: Safe response<br/>(or blocked with reason)
